<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="83" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="30" pageNumber="83">Geographical distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="30" pageNumber="83">
Known principally from the southern Nama-Karoo of South Africa. The single record from Zimbabwe suggests that further records are required to establish the distribution pattern. (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Distributions of collection records of Bembix spp.: a Bembix karroensis b Bembix liturata c Bembix loupata d Bembix melanopa e Bembix moebii f Bembix monedula." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11861" pageId="30" pageNumber="83">Fig. 12b</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
